Create a Dynamic Dashboard in Salesforce Classic

To provide individualized views of data, create a dynamic dashboard.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
Manage Dynamic Dashboards

Available in: Salesforce Classic
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

On the Dashboards tab, create a dashboard or edit an existing one.
Next to View Dashboard as, click  and select Run as logged-in user.
To let users change the dashboardâ€™s running user, select Let authorized users change running user on the dashboard view page.
Click OK.
For View dashboard as, enter a running user.
Save your dashboard.

Set the appropriate Show option on the report run page.
Avoid restricting the dashboard's view of data by not including specific record owners in an advanced filter or saving an opportunity report with hierarchy level.
